main event: An unidentified flying object was sighted over Sioux City, Iowa on January 23, 1951, described by multiple witnesses as cigar-shaped and emitting a white-yellow light.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 21 minutes,Prior reports indicated the object had characteristics similar to an aircraft but behaved erratically,Two airport control tower personnel confirmed the sighting and stated the object appeared to fly at high speeds and varied at altitudes of about 2000 feet to rapid ascents,Reports suggested that the object emitted little to no sound during its observation,The sightings were consistent with others reported in the region around the same timeframe.
sighted object: cigar-shaped object emitting a white-yellow light
witness description: airport control tower personnel and other observers in the area
